$ SQL*Plus: SET SHOWMODE
@ set showmode

If set to `on`, → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus will print the old and new value of an SQL*Plus system variable when modifying it with `set`.

code {
SQL> set long 42
SQL> set showmode on
new: showmode BOTH
SQL> set long 99
old: long 42
new: long 99
SQL> old: showmode BOTH
code }

sa:
  The → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/set[`set`] command.
